Definition: the degree of oxidation of an atom or ion or molecule
Example: for simple atoms or ions the oxidation number is equal to the ionic charge; the oxidation number of hydrogen is +1 and of oxygen is -2
Synonyms: oxidation_state, number, the, degree, of, oxidation, an, atom, or, ion, molecule, for, simple, atoms, ions, is, equal, to, ionic, charge, hydrogen, and, oxygen, -
Category: noun.quantity
